<!-- 1.5.12 -->
<div class='toload theorem'>
<p><span class='envidentifier'>Theorem 1.5.12
<span style='font-weight:normal;'>(Isomorphism Theorem for Boolean inverse semigroups)</span></span>
Let $\theta:S\to T$ be a morphism of Boolean inverse semigroups (as in Definition <span class='ref' data-tag='definitionmorphismofbooleaninversesemigroups'></span>) and $I\subseteq\theta^{-1}(0)$ a $\lor$-ideal. Then</p>
<ol class='alphpar'>
	<li> $\theta$ factors uniquely to a Boolean inverse semigroup morphism $\theta_I:S/I\to T$.</li>
	<li> $I=\theta^{-1}(0)$ if and only if $\theta_I$ is injective.</li>
</ol>
</div>